Upgrading to Univeral Analytics (from ga.js to analytics.js)
The event logging syntax changes from:
_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'category', 'action', 'opt_label', opt_value, opt_noninteraction]);
to:
ga('send', 'event', 'category', 'action', 'opt_label', opt_value, {'nonInteraction': 1});

_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', document.title, 'pay as you go', '{$SomeInternalVariable} credits']);
_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', asdf, jkl;, zxcv']);
_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'dashboard', 'kb link', 'special link']);
_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'dashboard', 'custom action', 'custom label']);

To swap _gaq.push with ga, _trackEvent with send, event and get rid of the square brackets, replace the match with:
ga('send', 'event', $1\)
